Banks to Lose Business to Hedge Funds on Rules, Telegraph Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-03-24T22:31:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-24/banks-to-lose-business-to-hedge-funds-on-rules-telegraph-says.html
New bank regulations will cause
business to move away from investment banks toward “non-bank”
institutions such as  hedge funds , private equity firms and
pension funds that aren’t subject to the rules, the Daily
Telegraph reported, citing a report by investment bank  Morgan
Stanley (MS)  and consulting firm Oliver Wyman.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 